166.text: Mehmet Yanik , a neurotechnology expert at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology ( MIT ) in Cambridge

83.text: Charles Lieber , a chemist at Harvard University in Cambridge , Massachusetts

31.text: a micrometre - scale glass pipette containing an electrode

127.text: a transistor that would be able to enter a cell and take electrical readings without causing too much harm

quotes.text: "This is literally the scale of the inner components of a cell,"
quotes.speaker: Lieber

quotes.text: "We're really blurring the distinction between what's an electrical probe and what is biological matter,"
quotes.speaker: Lieber

quotes.text: "That would be a breakthrough technology for neuroscience,"
quotes.speaker: Yanik

quotes.text: "The long-term idea is to make artificial tissue that is wired up and can be implanted to enhance medical monitoring,"
